Package commands

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Add
    The command pops two elements off the stack, adds them and puts result back on the stack
    Bridge
    The command that makes the next command to be skipped
    Command
    Abstract command class
    Divide
    The command pops two elements off the stack, divides the second by the first them and puts result back on the stack
    DoNothing
    The command that does nothing
    Dup
    The command pushed the last element of the stack onto the stack again
    End
    The command that stops the program
    Get
    The command that gets the top of the stack two elements x and y, and puts on the stack the value at these coordinates
    Greater
    The command pops two elements off the stack, compares them and puts 1 if first greater or 0 else
    HorizontalIf
    The command that turns the direction of the movement to the right if the last element of the stack is zero or to the left otherwise
    InputCharacter
    The function that takes a char-value from the user and pushed it onto the stack
    InputInt
    The command that takes a int-value from the user and pushed it onto the stack
    InStack
    The command that pushed number from the field onto the stack
    Modulo
    The command pops two elements off the stack, takes the modulus from dividing the second by the first them and puts result back on the stack
    Multiplication
    The command pops two elements off the stack, multiplies them and puts result back on the stack
    Not
    The command that pops a number from the top of the stack and if it is 0 then puts 1 on the stack or 0 otherwise
    OutputChar
    The command that pops an item off the top of the stack and prints its ascii character
    OutputInt
    The command that pops an item off the top of the stack and prints its numeric representation
    Pop
    The command that pops an item off the top of stack
    Put
    The command that takes three values from the top of stack: , and and changes the field of Befunge program value to by coordinates
    StringMode
    The command that turns on the line mode
    Subtraction
    The command pops two elements off the stack, subtracts the first by the second them and puts result back on the stack
    Swap
    The command pops two elements off the stack, swaps them and puts result back on the stack
    TurnDown
    The command that turns the direction of the movement to the down
    TurnLeft
    The command that turns the direction of the movement to the left
    TurnRandom
    The command that turns the direction of the movement to the random direction
    TurnRight
    The command that turns the direction of the movement to the right
    TurnUp
    The command that turns the direction of the movement to the up
    VerticalIf
    The command that turns the direction of the movement to the down if the last element of the stack is zero or to the up otherwise
